COPYING.provenance — per-file porting provenance for @session.js/groups
========================================================================

Status: P0 SCAFFOLD — no ported files yet. This record is filled in
per-file as implementation phases P3–P7 land, in the same format as
calls/COPYING.provenance.

License decision: everything shipped in this package is licensed
AGPL-3.0-or-later. Official Session clients are GPLv3 (session-android)
and AGPLv3 (session-desktop); GPLv3 code combines into an AGPLv3 work per
AGPLv3 §13. All upstream copyright notices will be preserved in the
headers of ported files, and changes annotated ("modified"), as GPL
requires. © of ported portions: Session Foundation.

Reference commits (docs/closed-groups/reference-pins.md):
  session-desktop  master   @ d86076b443bba73510c0f6b6124f5dbc59deb05c
  session-android  v1.19.1  @ e5ee2e1e1a72fd0b7229ff7385c52c3abb7b6d04

PORTED FILES
------------
src/keypairs.ts
  Ported from session-desktop `ts/receiver/closedGroups.ts`
  (master @ d86076b, AGPLv3): `getAllCachedECKeyPair`,
  `addKeyPairToCacheAndDBIfNeeded`, `removeAllClosedGroupEncryptionKeyPairs`
  (Kotlin analog: session-android `GroupUtil`/`ClosedGroup` keypair storage,
  GPLv3), © Session Foundation, modified (TypeScript; backed by GroupStorage
  instead of the desktop Data layer; unprefixed-hex keypairs; append/dedupe-
  by-value/latest semantics per IMPLEMENTATION.md §2.5). Licensed under
  AGPL-3.0-or-later.

src/group-manager.ts
  Group lifecycle wiring adapted from session-desktop
  `ts/session/group/closed-group.ts` and `ts/receiver/closedGroups.ts`
  (master @ d86076b, AGPLv3) and session-android `.../messaging/groups/
  ClosedGroup.kt` / `.../ReceivedMessageHandler.kt` (v1.19.1, GPLv3),
  © Session Foundation, modified (restructured onto a structural
  GroupSessionLike + GroupStorage + KeypairRegistry, following the
  @session.js/calls CallManager/CallSupervisor composition). Ports: formation
  + per-member NEW invites (P4), inbound NEW gates + group chat send/receive
  (P5), and the member lifecycle — add/NEW-invite + admin keypair-push,
  admin-only remove + ENCRYPTION_KEY_PAIR rotation, leave/zombie/admin-disband,
  rename, and the performIfValid receive gates: watermark, sender-∈-members,
  admin-only removal, first-admin-not-removable (P6); multi-device legacy
  ConfigurationMessage reconciliation — join missing / overwrite / delete
  absent (P7, desktop ts/receiver/configMessage.ts analog). Licensed under
  AGPL-3.0-or-later.

Expected remaining porting surface (IMPLEMENTATION.md §5, filled in P4–P7):
  src/handlers.ts          — inbound control dispatch adapted from
                             ts/receiver/closedGroups.ts (AGPLv3) and
                             .../sending_receiving/ReceivedMessageHandler.kt (GPLv3)

